docs.abstract: Residents rarely learn how data centers and their noise and energy and water use may affect their lives until it’s too late.
docs.snippet: Residents rarely learn how data centers and their noise and energy and water use may affect their lives until it’s too late.
docs.lead_paragraph: The revolution in artificial intelligence that promised us breakthroughs in medical research and corporate productivity seems to be running a little behind. But already A.I. has become something of a nightmare for the Americans who happen to live near one of the more than 5,000 data centers that power it and keep the cloud above our digital world running.

headline.main: Noisy, Hungry Data Centers Are Catching Communities by Surprise

docs.abstract: This taut and serious Amazon series chronicles the time when Prince Andrew was interviewed on TV about his relationship with Jeffrey Epstein.
docs.snippet: This taut and serious Amazon series chronicles the time when Prince Andrew was interviewed on TV about his relationship with Jeffrey Epstein.
docs.lead_paragraph: “A Very Royal Scandal,” available now on Amazon Prime Video, tells — retells — the story of when the BBC journalist Emily Maitlis interviewed Prince Andrew on television in 2019 about his relationship to Jeffrey Epstein. The very first thing he says in the interview is that “there is no good time to talk about Mr. Epstein and all things associated.” Welp …

headline.main: ‘A Very Royal Scandal’ Is a Juicy British Drama
headline.print_headline: A Juicy Yet Serious British Drama About Royal Hubris

docs.abstract: A group of people who participated in the reality competition show this summer are suing MrBeast’s production company.
docs.snippet: A group of people who participated in the reality competition show this summer are suing MrBeast’s production company.
docs.lead_paragraph: A group of contestants who participated in “Beast Games,” the reality competition show hosted by Jimmy Donaldson, better known online as MrBeast, are suing Mr. Donaldson and the production companies behind the show, accusing them of exposing participants to “dangerous circumstances and conditions.”

headline.main: ‘Beast Games’ Contestants File Lawsuit Claiming ‘Dangerous Conditions’ on Set

docs.abstract: The internet giant told employees on Monday that it expected them to return to the office full-time in January.
docs.snippet: The internet giant told employees on Monday that it expected them to return to the office full-time in January.
docs.lead_paragraph: Amazon told its corporate employees on Monday that they had to return to working in the company’s offices five days a week starting in January.

headline.main: Amazon Tells Corporate Workers to Be Back in the Office 5 Days a Week
headline.print_headline: Amazon Sends Corporate Staff Back to Office

byline.original: By Karen Weise and Emma Goldberg

docs.abstract: From hurricanes to wildfires, a new generation of technologies could help utilities better plan for the risk of extreme weather to their electric grid.
docs.snippet: From hurricanes to wildfires, a new generation of technologies could help utilities better plan for the risk of extreme weather to their electric grid.
docs.lead_paragraph: More than 4 million people were without power on Friday morning after the enormous ring of wind and rain known as Hurricane Helene made landfall in Florida and moved north.

headline.main: Extreme Weather Is Taxing Utilities More Often. Can A.I. Help?
headline.print_headline: Utilities See A.I. as Way To Fix Grid

docs.abstract: “They should have just called it Strawberry. At least that’s delicious.”
docs.snippet: “They should have just called it Strawberry. At least that’s delicious.”
docs.lead_paragraph: Last week, OpenAI released a preview of its hotly anticipated new model, o1. We discuss what it has excelled at and how it could accelerate the timeline for building superintelligence. Then, we explain why Meta is making teenagers’ Instagram accounts private by default. And, finally, we chat with the New York Times reporter Karen Weise about why Amazon is forcing its corporate employees to go back to working in the office five days a week and whether other companies will follow suit.

headline.main: OpenAI’s Reasoning Machine, Instagram Teen Changes and Amazon R.T.O. Drama

byline.original: By Kevin Roose, Casey Newton, Whitney Jones, Rachel Cohn, Jen Poyant, Daniel Ramirez, Dan Powell, Elisheba Ittoop, Marion Lozano and Rowan Niemisto

docs.abstract: Under pressure from Chinese competitors, Amazon, Walmart and other U.S. retailers have been exploring ways to avoid tariffs. Could a new Biden administration rule change that?
docs.snippet: Under pressure from Chinese competitors, Amazon, Walmart and other U.S. retailers have been exploring ways to avoid tariffs. Could a new Biden administration rule change that?
docs.lead_paragraph: Major American retailers including Amazon and Walmart have been quietly exploring shifting toward a business model that would ship more goods directly to consumers from Chinese factories and require fewer U.S. workers in retail stores and logistics centers.

headline.main: New Tariff Rules Could Reverse a ‘Paradigm Shift’ in Retail
headline.print_headline: New Tariff Rules Could Turn Tide on Direct Retail Shipping From China

byline.original: By Ana Swanson and Jordyn Holman

docs.abstract: The chipmaker, which has been struggling, said on Monday that it obtained a new government grant, signed a contract with Amazon and would pause some initiatives.
docs.snippet: The chipmaker, which has been struggling, said on Monday that it obtained a new government grant, signed a contract with Amazon and would pause some initiatives.
docs.lead_paragraph: Intel, a Silicon Valley giant that has struggled after a series of stumbles, said on Monday that it had signed new contracts and made further belt-tightening plans as it tries to cope with a deep slump in its business.

headline.main: Intel, Aiming to Reverse Slump, Unveils New Contracts and Cost Cuts
headline.print_headline: Intel Awarded $3 Billion to Expand Manufacturing of Advanced Semiconductors for U.S. Military
